{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Using convolutional neural network (CNN) classifiers, Gakhar et al. (2020) demonstrated that surface elevation information alone can be used to determine the physical features at the bottom boundary (see also Mandel et al. 2017; Gakhar, Koseff & Ouellette 2022).",
    "More recently, Xuan & Shen (2023) explored the feasibility of using a CNN to reconstruct the turbulent flow beneath free-surface flows using the surface elevation and velocity (see also Li, Xuan & Shen 2020).",
    "Their CNN-based model was trained on a dataset obtained from DNSs of turbulent open-channel flows over a deformable surface and could accurately reconstruct the near-surface flow field.",
    "In the absence of accurate parameterizations of the sea-surface drag (see, for e.g.",
    "Sullivan & McWilliams 2010; Zachry et al. 2013; Gao et al. 2020), ML-based approaches may thus offer a practical alternative."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
